-- Citigroup second-quarter earnings fall 37 percent
-- 
-- Fri Jul 16, 2010 8:32am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/07/16/us-citigroup-idUSTRE66F26U20100716

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Citigroup Inc ( C.N ) posted a $2.7 billion quarterly profit, down 37 percent from the same quarter last year, hurt by lower revenue in its investment banking business. 

 The third-largest U.S. bank posted second-quarter profit of 9 cents a share, compared with $4.28 billon, or 49 cents a share, a year earlier. Analysts on average expected 5 cents a share before special items, according to Reuters Estimates. Through Thursday's stock market close, the company's shares had risen 26 percent this year, while the broader U.S. banking sector .BKX had risen 17 percent. (Reporting by  Dan Wilchins ; editing by John Wallace)